                                    7321                     Ÿ    NLIST - PARAMETER NAME LIST (AS DEFINED ON PROC STATEMENT)   Ÿ
                                    7322                     Ÿ    VLIST - PARAMETER VALUE LIST                                 Ÿ
                                    7323                     Ÿ  PLIST - PARAMETER NAME LIST (AS SPECIFIED ON PCALL STATEMENT)  Ÿ
                                    7324                     Ÿ                                                                 Ÿ
                                    7325                     Ÿ    NOTE: THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN A NLIST AND A PLIST (IN THIS    Ÿ
                                    7326                     Ÿ    PROGRAM) IS AS FOLLOWS:  A NLIST IS A LIST OF NAMES          Ÿ
                                    7327                     Ÿ    SPECIFIED ON A PROCEDURE DEFINITION,, THE NAMES MUST         Ÿ
                                    7328                     Ÿ    SIMPLE VARIABLE NAMES.  THESE VARIABLES WILL BECOME          Ÿ
                                    7329                     Ÿ    LOCAL VARIABLES OF THE PROCEDURE.  A PLIST IS A LIST         Ÿ
                                    7330                     Ÿ    OF PARM VARIABLE NAMES THAT ARE PASSED TO A PROCEDURE,, AS   Ÿ
                                    7331                     Ÿ    SOME OF THE PARAMETERS MAY BE EXPRESSIONS OR CONSTANTS       Ÿ
                                    7332                     Ÿ    NOT ALL THE ENTRIES IN A PLIST EXIST,, ONLY VARIABLE         Ÿ
                                    7333                     Ÿ    NAME ENTRIES EXIST,,, CONSTANT OR EXPRESSION ENTRIES ARE     Ÿ
                                    7334                     Ÿ    ZERO.                                                        Ÿ

0                                   7592              ¿þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþÜ
                                    7593              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                    7594              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                    7595              Ÿ  XCALL - CALL EXEC FILE                                             Ÿ
                                    7596              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                    7597              Ÿ  ON ENTRY:                                                          Ÿ
                                    7598              Ÿ       SCANCB - REMAINDER OF XCALL COMMAND !                         Ÿ
                                    7599              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                    7600              Ÿ  WE DO THE FOLLOWING (MORE OR LESS) !                               Ÿ
                                    7601              Ÿ       - GET THE NAME OF THE EXEC TO CALL                            Ÿ
                                    7602              Ÿ       - LOAD THE EXEC TO CALL, IF NOT ALREADY LOADED                Ÿ
                                    7603              Ÿ       - GET THE PARAMETER STRING                                    Ÿ
                                    7604              Ÿ       - GET THE PARAMETER LIST                                      Ÿ
                                    7605              Ÿ       - GET THE PARAMETER VALUES                                    Ÿ
                                    7606              Ÿ       - GET THE XPROC NAME LIST                                     Ÿ
                                    7607              Ÿ       - PASS PARAMETERS                                             Ÿ
                                    7608              Ÿ       - SAVE CALLING/CALLED PARM LISTS                              Ÿ
                                    7609              Ÿ       - SAVE CALLING ROUTINES EXECUTION STATE                       Ÿ
                                    7610              Ÿ       - ESTABLISH NEW ROUTINES EXECUTION STATE                      Ÿ
                                    7611              Ÿ       - TAKE OFF !                                                  Ÿ
                                    7612              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                    7613              Ÿ NOTE: CPPLIMIT=8                MAXIMUM NUMBER OF PARAMETERS        Ÿ
                                    7614              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                    7615              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                                      ¾þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþ»

0                                  11076              *-box
                                   11077              *
                                   11078              *  XCLEANUP
                                   11079              *
                                   11080              *  THIS ROUTINE OFFERS US A CHANCE TO DO ANY NECESSARY
                                   11081              *  CLEANUP AT THE TIME THAT AN XPROC RETURNS.  THOUGH
                                   11082              *  SOMEDAY THIS ROUTINE MAY HAVE SOME MORE GENERAL PURPOSE
                                   11083              *  FOR NOW IT SIMPLY CHECKS THE DUMP STATUS INFORMATION,
                                   11084              *  AND WRITES A 'LINE NNNN IS LAST LINE' MESSAGE IF
                                   11085              *  APPROPRIATE.
                                   11086              *
                                   11087              *  ON ENTRY:
                                   11088              *        R1 - THE NEW STATE FLAGS,
                                   11089              *        CP - CONTAINS THE CURRENT STATE
                                   11090              *
                                   11091              *  ON EXIT:
                                   11092              *        NO RETURNS,  WILL WRITE 'LINE NNNN IS LAST LINE' IF
                                   11093              *        APPROPRIATE DUMP STUFF IS TURNED ON.
                                   11094              *
 000D26 50E0 D000/9008_      00000 11095              XCLEANUP PROC  ,
 USING  *,R7
 USING  SNENTRY,R6                 11134                       USING SNENTRY,R6
 000D40 1861                       11143                       LR    R6,R1
                                   11144
                                   11145                       COMMENT                   CHECK TO SEE IF WE
                                   11146                       COMMENT                   SHOULD WRITE DUMP MSG
 000D42 9180 B7E4/47E0_007E4       11147                       IF    (CPFXDUMP,AND,~SNFEXEC,AND,SNFTYPED),BEGIN
 000D5A 5820 B7E8            007E8 11188  1                      L     R2,CPXDPLN
 000D5E 1222/47D0 707C             11189  1                      IF    (R2,POS),BEGIN
 000D64 1B00/41F0 B050_            11203  2                        TWRITE
 000D70 947F B7E4      007E4       11228  2                        CLEAR CPFXDUMP
 000D74 4110 7398/4100_      010D8 11235  2                        TSEG  'Line '
 000D86 5800 B7E8            007E8 11253  2                        L     R0,CPXDPLN
 000D8A 58E0 72F4/0DEE       01034 11254  2                        VCALL CVEXNO
 000D90 41F0 B050/58E0_      00050 11258  2                        TSEG  (R1),(R0)
 000D9A 4110 7304/4100_      01044 11282  2                        TSEG  ' is the last line.'
 000DAC 1B00/41F0 B050_            11300  2                        TWRITE
 000DB8 9680 B7E4      007E4       11325  2                        SET   CPFXDUMP
 000DBC                            11331  1                      END
 000DBC                            11335                       END

                                   15696              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ

                                   18708              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   18709              Ÿ  XFORMAT - FORMAT EXTENDED EXEC FILE                                Ÿ
                                   18710              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   18711              Ÿ  ON ENTRY:                                                          Ÿ
                                   18712              Ÿ       SCAN CONTROL BLOCK - REMAINDER OF COMMAND                     Ÿ
                                   18713              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   18714              Ÿ  ON EXIT:                                                           Ÿ
                                   18715              Ÿ       ACTIVE FILE FORMATTED AS REQUESTED                            Ÿ
                                   18716              Ÿ       ALL ERRORS EXIT VIA CVERROR                                   Ÿ
                                   18717              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   18718              Ÿ  THIS ROUTINE ROUTINES WORKS AS FOLLOWS,  FIRST WE DO THE           Ÿ
                                   18719              Ÿ  EQUIVALENT OF AN XSCAN,  THIS IS TO INSURE THAT ALL BEGIN/         Ÿ
                                   18720              Ÿ  END BLOCK ARE SYNTACTICALLY CORRECT.  WE THEN CALL FFORMAT         Ÿ
                                   18721              Ÿ  (IN FLOW MODULE) TO FORMAT EXEC.  THERE ARE MANY ROUTINES          Ÿ
                                   18722              Ÿ  FOR PARSING BEGIN-END BLOCKS IN FLOW MODULE, SO THAT IS            Ÿ
                                   18723              Ÿ  WHY MOST OF THE WORK (FFORMAT ROUTINE) IS DONE THERE.              Ÿ

                                   19406              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   19407              Ÿ  XXXEXIT - RESET XPROC ENVIRONMENT, AND GOTO XPROC LABEL            Ÿ
                                   19408              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   19409              Ÿ  ON ENTRY:                                                          Ÿ
                                   19410              Ÿ       R0 - LINE NUMBER OF XPROC LABEL                               Ÿ
                                   19411              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   19412              Ÿ  ON EXIT:                                                           Ÿ
                                   19413              Ÿ       THIS ROUTINE DOES NOT RETURN.  IT CALLS THE START ROUTINE     Ÿ
                                   19414              Ÿ       TO RESET THE EXEC ENVIRONMENT AND START UP AT THE NEW LINE    Ÿ
                                   19415              Ÿ       NUMBER.  IT DOES NOT RETURN.                                  Ÿ
                                   19416              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   19417              Ÿ  NOTE:                                                              Ÿ
                                   19418              Ÿ       'XEXIT' ENTRY POINT IS IN FLOW MODULE.  WE COME HERE TO       Ÿ
                                   19419              Ÿ       RESET XPROC ENVIRIONMENT AND START UP XPROC AT LINE NUMBER    Ÿ
                                   19420              Ÿ       PASSED TO US FROM 'XEXIT' ROUTINE. THIS ROUTINE DOES NOT      Ÿ
                                   19421              Ÿ       RETURN.!!                                                     Ÿ
                                   19422              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   19423              Ÿ       THIS ROUTINE CHAINS BACK THROUGH ALL THE PROC STATE           Ÿ
                                   19424              Ÿ       INFORMATION.  WHEN IT REACHES THE XPROC STATE (ENVIRONMENT)   Ÿ
                                   19425              Ÿ       INFORMATION, IT MODIFIES IT TO CONTAIN THE NEW LABEL LINE     Ÿ
                                   19426              Ÿ       NUMBER AS THE NEXT LINE NUMBER TO EXECUTE, AND THEN STARTS    Ÿ
                                   19427              Ÿ       UP THE EXEC WITH THE XPROC ENVIRONMENT !                      Ÿ
                                   19428              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   19429              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ

                                   21452              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   21453              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   21454              Ÿ  UPDTINFO - UPDATE PUBLIC EXEC INFO                                 Ÿ
                                   21455              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   21456              Ÿ  ON ENTRY:                                                          Ÿ
                                   21457              Ÿ      @R1 - EXEC INFO DSECT (OLD), ALL FIELDS FILLED                 Ÿ
                                   21458              Ÿ      @R2 - EXEC INFO DSECT (NEW), ALL FIELDS FILLED                 Ÿ

                                   21461              Ÿ       DONE.                                                         Ÿ
                                   21462              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   21463              Ÿ  THIS ROUTINE UPDATES PUBLIC EXEC FILE INFO.  IT IS USED WHEN       Ÿ
                                   21464              Ÿ  A PUBLIC EXEC IS REPLACED.  THE OLD EXEC CAN NOT BE DELETED        Ÿ
                                   21465              Ÿ  SOMEONE MAY STILL BE POINTED TO IT.  SO INSTEAD WE MARK IT         Ÿ
                                   21466              Ÿ  WITH A DIFFERENT NAME AND KEEP IT AROUND.  THIS ROUTINE SETS       Ÿ
                                   21467              Ÿ  UP BOTH THE NEW AND OLD NAMES AND INDEXES.  CARE IS TAKEN TO       Ÿ
                                   21468              Ÿ  ORDER THE INFO UPDATES SO THAT THE INFO IS ALWAYS CONSISTENT!      Ÿ
                                   21469              Ÿ  (IE. OLD MARKED ENTRY SAVED, NEW INDEX ENTRY SAVED, OLD INDEX      Ÿ
                                   21470              Ÿ  UPDATED, NEW ENTRY REPLACES OLD ENTRY,,, DIG IT !)                 Ÿ
                                   21471              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ

0                                  21858              ¿þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþÜ
                                   21859              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   21860              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   21861              Ÿ  GETXRG - GET EXEC RECORD GROUP DSECT POINTER                       Ÿ
                                   21862              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   21863              Ÿ  ON ENTRY:                                                          Ÿ
                                   21864              Ÿ       R0 - SET NUMBER                                               Ÿ
                                   21865              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   21866              Ÿ  ON EXIT:                                                           Ÿ
                                   21867              Ÿ       R1 - EXEC RECORD GROUP POINTER (ZERO IF R15=NZ)               Ÿ
                                   21868              Ÿ       R15 - CC=Z, VALID SET NUMBER                                  Ÿ
                                   21869              Ÿ             CC=NZ, NON-USED SET NUMBER                              Ÿ
                                   21870              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   21871              Ÿ  NOTE:  THIS ROUTINE WORKS LIKE THIS, AS OF 1/1/87..                Ÿ
                                   21872              Ÿ       1-2048 (CV#FEXEC) ARE USER EXECS                              Ÿ
                                   21873              Ÿ       2048+  ARE PUBLIC EXEC NUMBERS                                Ÿ
                                   21874              Ÿ  THE IDEA IS BY ASSIGNING DIFFERENT RANGES OF SET NUMBERS,          Ÿ
                                   21875              Ÿ  THE SET NUMBER UNIQUELY DEFINES THE EXEC, PRIOR TO 1/1/87          Ÿ
                                   21876              Ÿ  BOTH THE SET NUMBER AND EXEC RECORD GROUP NUMBER WERE              Ÿ
                                   21877              Ÿ  ALWAYS SPECIFIED TOGETHER,,, AND THAT IS THE WAY THEY ARE          Ÿ
                                   21878              Ÿ  GENERALLY USED WITHIN THIS MODULE.  IN ANY CASE, FOR NOW,          Ÿ
                                   21879              Ÿ  GIVEN AN EXEC SET NUMBER, THIS ROUTINE WILL RETURN THE             Ÿ
                                   21880              Ÿ  RECORD GROUP INFO DSECT POINTER. YEOW!                             Ÿ
                                   21881              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   21882              Ÿ  NOTE2: R15 REFLECTS ONLY WEAK TESTING OF SET NUMBER SPACE.         Ÿ
                                   21883              Ÿ  IT DOES NOT TELL IF AN ACTUAL EXEC EXISTS.                         Ÿ
                                   21884              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   21885              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                                      ¾þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþ»

0                                  22645              *
                                   22646              **
                                   22647              **  XLISTCLR - CLEAR EXEC SET NUMBER LIST, CALLED AT SIGN-ON
                                   22648              **
                                   22649              **  WE KEEP A LARGE CACHE OF THE MOST RECENTLY USED EXEC FILES
                                   22650              **  FOR EACH USER.  THE CACHE WORKS ON A 'LRU' SCHEEME.  THAT
                                   22651              **  IS IF THE CACHE FILLS UP WE MOVE THE LRU EXEC FILE.  THE
                                   22652              **  LRU SCEEME IS IMPLEMENTED BY AN ORDERED LIST OF EXEC FILES
                                   22653              **  WITH THE MOST RECENTLY USED AT THE HEAD OF THE LIST.  ENTRIES
                                   22654              **  IN THE LIST CAN RANGE FROM 1-256 WITH ZERO AS A NULL ENTRY.
                                   22655              **  IF THE CACHE IS FULL THE LRU EXEC IS PURGED AND THE NEW EXEC
                                   22656              **  TAKES ON ITS 'EXEC SET NUMBER'.  EACH TIME AN EXEC IS LOADED
                                   22657              **  OR CALLED IT IS MOVED (MARKED) TO THE START OF THE LIST AND
                                   22658              **  ALL OTHER ENTRIES ARE MOVED BACK ONE.
                                   22659              **
                                   22660              **
                                   22661              **  NOTE: THESE ROUTINES ARE FOR USE ONLY WITH USER EXEC FILES.
                                   22662              **        PUBLIC EXEC FILES ARE NEVER DELETED AND ARE ALLOCATED
                                   22663              **        NEW SETS IN ORDER, 1 TO 30000+.
                                   22664              **
                                   22665              **
                                   22666              XLISTCNT EQU   256 CPMAXXCT        MAXIMUM ELEMENTS IN LIST
                                   22667              XLISTLEN EQU   XLISTCNT*4          LENGTH OF LIST
                                   22668              XLFIRST  EQU   CP#FEXEC            FIRST ALLOWABLE EXEC SET NUMBER
                                   22669
 000000                00000 00404 22670              XLISTWA  RECORD BEGIN ,
 000000                            22678  1           XLSETNO    DS    F                   SET NUMBER
 000004                            22679  1           XLLIST     DS    XL(XLISTLEN)        SET LIST
 000404                00404 00400 22680  1                      ORG   XLLIST+XLISTLEN-4
 000400                            22681  1           XLISTEND   DS    F                   LAST ENTRY (LRU) IN LIST
 000404                00404 00404 22682                       END
                                   22691              *
                                   22692              *
 0036D0 50E0 D000/9008_      00000 22693              XLISTCLR XPROC XLISTWA
 USING  *,R7
 USING  XLISTWA-(4+36),R8
 0036EA D7FF 802C 802C_00004 00004 22744                       CLEAR XLLIST              CLEAR EXEC LRU LIST
                                   22754

 003706 4110 802C            00004 22757                       LA    R1,XLLIST
 00370A 4120 7446            03B30 22758                       LA    R2,=CL16'SYS.XSETLIST    '

                                   22763

0                                  28643              ¿þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþÜ
                                   28644              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   28645              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   28646              Ÿ  SCNPLIST - EVALUATE PROCEDURE CALL PARAMETERS (INTO NAMES)         Ÿ
                                   28647              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   28648              Ÿ  WE SCAN FOR PARMS THAT ARE VALID VARIABLES AS WELL AS              Ÿ
                                   28649              Ÿ  VALUES. THESE ENTRIES FORM A PARM LIST THAT IS USED IF             Ÿ
                                   28650              Ÿ  WHEN RETURNING FROM A PROC/XPROC CALL.  WE SCAN BY                 Ÿ
                                   28651              Ÿ  SCANNING EACH PARM AS A VALUE AND AS A DESCRIPTOR. IF              Ÿ
                                   28652              Ÿ  THE TWO ARE EQUAL WE HAVE A PARM AS A NAME AND PUT IT              Ÿ
                                   28653              Ÿ  IN THE LIST TO BE USED IF VAIABLES ARE RETURED.  ONE               Ÿ
                                   28654              Ÿ  EXTRA POINT,  GENERIC ARRAYS (IE. X[]) ARE VALID AND               Ÿ
                                   28655              Ÿ  ARE HANDLED BY USING SCNPDESC AND EVALPARM,, INSTEAD OF            Ÿ
                                   28656              Ÿ  SCNVDESC AND EVALEXPR ROUTINES.  THINK ABOUT IT, BUD.              Ÿ
                                   28657              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   28658              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   28659              Ÿ  ON ENTRY:                                                          Ÿ
                                   28660              Ÿ       R0 - LENGTH OF REMAINING EXPRESSION                           Ÿ
                                   28661              Ÿ       R1 - START OF PARM LIST, (STARTS WITH "(")                    Ÿ
                                   28662              Ÿ       R2 - RETURN AREA FOR PARAMETER NAME LIST                      Ÿ
                                   28663              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   28664              Ÿ  ON EXIT:                                                           Ÿ
                                   28665              Ÿ       R0 - PARAMETER COUNT (SEE NOTE)                               Ÿ
                                   28666              Ÿ      R15 - CC=ZERO, ALL OK                                          Ÿ
                                   28667              Ÿ            ALL ERRORS EXIT VIA CVERROR                              Ÿ
                                   28668              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   28669              Ÿ  REGISTER USAGE:                                                    Ÿ
                                   28670              Ÿ       R1,R0 - STRING LOCATION,LENGTH                                Ÿ
                                   28671              Ÿ       R3 - VALUE COUNT                                              Ÿ
                                   28672              Ÿ       R6 - VALUE RETURN LIST INDEX                                  Ÿ
                                   28673              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   28674              Ÿ  NOTE: NAME COUNT IS -1 IF FREE FORM PARAMETER.                     Ÿ
                                   28675              Ÿ        NAME COUNT IS 0 IF NONE.                                     Ÿ

                                   28677              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   28678              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ

                                   29499              Ÿ  SCNPDESC - SCAN PARMATER NAME (DESCRIPTOR)                         Ÿ
                                   29500              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   29501              Ÿ  THIS ROUTINE SCANS VARIABLE NAMES, AND IN THE CASE OF              Ÿ
                                   29502              Ÿ  AN ARRAY, IT'S SUBSCRIPTS.  SEE VNDESC IN VNENTRY DSECT.           Ÿ
                                   29503              Ÿ  ONLY NAME SYNTAX IS CHECKED, WHILE SUBSCRIPTS ARE EVALUATED.       Ÿ
                                   29504              Ÿ  THIS ROUTINE DIFFERS FROM SCNVDESC IN THAT IT ALLOWS               Ÿ
                                   29505              Ÿ  GENERIC ARRAY ENTRIES (EG. X[], TEST2[])                           Ÿ
                                   29506              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ

                                   34026              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ

                                   34029              Ÿ  AN XPROC LEVEL.  SO ON RETURN FROM A PCALL WE MUST                 Ÿ

                                   35127              Ÿ  ON ENTRY:                                                          Ÿ

                                   35129              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ

                                   35131              Ÿ       R15 - CC=ZERO                                                 Ÿ
                                   35132              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                   35133              Ÿ  EXPLANATION:  IF WE RELOAD A PUB EXEC WE NEED TO CHANGE THE        Ÿ
                                   35134              Ÿ  NAME OF THE OLD EXEC.  THIS WAY IT WILL STILL BE THERE FOR         Ÿ
                                   35135              Ÿ  PEOPLE WHO HAVE POINTERS TO IT.  AND NEW CALLERS CAN GET THE       Ÿ
                                   35136              Ÿ  NEW VERSION.  WE MARK THE NAME WITH THE SET # OF THE EXEC,         Ÿ
                                   35137              Ÿ  THIS NUMBER CREATES A UNIQUE NAME FOR EACH RELOADED EXEC,          Ÿ
                                   35138              Ÿ  ALSO IT PLACED IN SUCH A LOCATION AS TO NOT BE PRINTED OUT         Ÿ
